author: Russell Brand
description:
A mother of two is jailed in the UK over a social media post, sparking international outrage. As Charlie Kirk and JD Vance weigh in, Russell asks: Is Britain sliding into authoritarianism? From thought crimes to silent prayer bans, and growing U.S. concern over UK free speech laws, it's time to confront the chilling erosion of civil liberties. Are we protecting society—or just punishing dissent?
